{"PARD":[{"def":"A leopard; a panther.","pos":""}],"PARDALE":[{"def":"Certainly; surely; truly; verily; -- originally an oath.","pos":""}],"PARDINE":[{"def":"Spotted like a pard.","pos":""}],"PARDO":[{"def":"A money of account in Goa, India, equivalent to about 2s.","pos":""}],"PARDON":[{"def":"A release, by a sovereign, or officer having jurisdiction, from the penalties of an offense, being distinguished from amenesty, which is a general obliteration and canceling of a particular line of past offenses.","pos":""}],"PARDONABLE":[{"def":"Admitting of pardon; not requiring the excution of penalty; venial; excusable; -- applied to the offense or to the offender; as, a pardonable fault, or culprit.","pos":""}],"PARDONABLENESS":[{"def":"The quality or state of being pardonable; as, the pardonableness of sin.","pos":""}],"PARDONABLY":[{"def":"In a manner admitting of pardon; excusably.","pos":""}],"PARDONER":[{"def":"One who pardons.","pos":""},{"def":"A seller of indulgences.","pos":""}],"PARDONING":[{"def":"Relating to pardon; having or exercising the right to pardon; willing to pardon; merciful; as, the pardoning power; a pardoning God.","pos":""}]}